1.title: Operation: Noob!
1.plot: When the Benevolent Alliance plans an all-out attack on the one virus-planet they know the location of, the Supernoobs need to learn how to fly Alliance issue Battle Jets.

2.title: Micro Noobs!
2.plot: Kevin has super-powered virus infected fleas, so the Supernoobs shrink down to face off against these small but mighty foes.

3.title: The Chosen Noob
3.plot: The Noobs learn of an ancient prophecy of a chosen warrior that will bring peace to the universe. They all think they are it. Rovu, a rival of the Noobs is pretty sure he is the chosen one, he arrives to earth to prove it.

4.title: Dude or Noob?
4.plot: Shope buys a pop-teen magazine, so she can learn how to connect with her female classmates.

5.title: Noob-A-Rella
5.plot: The Cornbury Snooty Society invites Shope to the annual Robot Scholarship Ball by mistake. Mem and Zen decided to get Shope in regardless. The party is crashed by the virus. The Noobs face off against a powerful foe.

6.title: The Noob Kids at School
6.plot: Mem and Zen are tired of the Noobs being late for training. The Noobs explain its hard to be a superhero and a student. Mem and Zen transform themselves into Robby and Bobby and learn school is harder then they thought.

7.title: High Noob
7.plot: The Creators invent a new virus, that goes back in time to destroy the earth before the Noobs are born. The Noobs travel back in time to face the virus.

8.title: Ring Around the Noob
8.plot: Mr. Badpants the worlds greatest wrestler is in town. The Noobs decide to challenge Mr. Badpants, using their battleballs. Mr. Badpants gets infected with a virus and they see how bad his pants can really be.

9.title: Noob Storm Rising!
9.plot: Zen and Mem are experiencing their second snow day. The Noobs teach them the art of making snowmen. Before long Mem and Zen vow to create the best snowman in history.

10.title: Noob of the Month
10.plot: Mem and Zen have to choose a Noob of the month. The winner gets a plaque and a special surprise prize. The competition gets heated and Kevin is suspected of cheating.

11.title: Supernoobs vs. Supertights!
11.plot: Count Venamus develops a dastardly plan: turn the Noobs' favorite super hero on them.

12.title: Pool Party Noob
12.plot: Tyler throws a pool party to hang out with his crush Amy. He promises the super cool SuperDoods will be there.

13.title: The Dark Noob Rises
13.plot: The Creators have found a way to corrupt Battleballs. Venamus uses the new knowledge to turn Shope, Kevin and Roach into Dark Warriors.

14.title: Noobs Down Under
14.plot: Strange tremors shake Cornbury, the byproduct of Venamus attempt to turn earth into a virus-creating planet.

15.title: Noobs Battle Balls
15.plot: The Noobs download a game that infest the Galacticus and XR4Ti; chaos follows.

16.title: The Noob Trap
16.plot: Roach's mom and dad get in a kung fu battle over who looks better in red. Roach's dad is sent out to camp in the yard. The Noobs help get them back together.

17.title: All Mixed Up and Nowhere to Noob
17.plot: The gang upgrade their battleballs, but something is extremely wrong. They have to fix it before a giant snail consumes Galacticus.

18.title: Call of Nooby
18.plot: The Noobs buy the game Andromeda Drop. A giant mecha battle game. Kevin suggests they use a virus and bring the mecha out of the TV and play with them for realsies. Shope thinks it's a bad idea. Too late, Kevin already did it.

19.title: The Noob John B!
19.plot: Mem and Zen need first hand research on Yachting. Kevin is super scared of the ocean. He turns to a pelican and flee only to see his friends swallowed virus infected whale. To rescue his friends he has to get over his fear of the ocean.

20.title: Noob Most Wanted
20.plot: Tyler has a doppelganger that is an interplanetary cat burglar. The interplanetary police have come to arrest Tyler. The Noobs must prove him innocent and catch Crony 12- Fingers.

21.title: Noob and Noober
21.plot: Venamus hacks the Battleballs making the Noobs super stupid. Mem and Zen have to find a way make the Noobs un-stupid.

22.title: A Noob's Best Friend
22.plot: Shope is trying to convince her parents she's ready for a dog. To persuade them Kevin turns into a stray dog. Kevin loves being a dog.

23.title: Noobie Noobie Boo!
23.plot: When a lake monster starts prowling Cornbury's beloved campground, the campers all leave, and the Supernoobs investigate.

24.title: If It Ain't Broke, Don't Noob It!
24.plot: The Noobs decided to make their balls look cooler and paint them. This breaks them, official Battleballs are on backorder. The Noobs must track down the Ball Master to fix their balls before a virus tracks them down and crushes them.

25.title: One Noob Wonder
25.plot: The Noobs want to become more popular. Kevin thinks the only way is through writing pop songs. Mem and Zen pretend to be super producers and try to sabotage the Noobs so they can keep training. This makes them more popular.

26.title: Noob 4 Mayor!
26.plot: The mayor of Cornbury is shucked out of office after it surfaces he hates corn. Rob and Bob decide to run for mayor, and the Noobs become divided only to realize politics ruin friendship.

27.title: Fluper Noobs
27.plot: Mem and Zen get the flu, making their trainers super weak and suitable to space viruses. Mem and Zen are taken over and become virus beasts. The Noobs must face off against their trainers before things get out of hand.

28.title: Cave Noobs!!
28.plot: The Noobs discover a caveman atop Mount McCorn who is infected with a virus. They defeat the virus and disguise him as Uncle Harry. This works until he steals from a museum and goes on the run.

29.title: Beam Me Up, Nooby
29.plot: Mr. Wertz erases everyone's minds and proclaims he is the ruler of Cornbury. The Supernoobs with the help of Mem and Zen and some friendly aliens have to save the dumbest town in history from hurting itself.

30.title: Spooker Noobs!
30.plot: The Supernoobs answer a survey about their biggest fears, only to find out the survey was orchestrated by Venamus.

31.title: Noob Raider
31.plot: A virus pod lands in the Amazon. The Noobs race south to stop it before it can infect all the jungle animals.

32.title: Get Your License Re-Noobed!
32.plot: Mem and Zen fall under scrutiny from the Benevolent Alliance, and have to renew their recruiter license or the Noobs will be taken away.

33.title: 20,000 Noobs Under the Sea
33.plot: The Noobs are given super underwater suits. They decided to find buried treasure to save the Cornbury Oceanography Center.

34.title: Noobing Down the House!
34.plot: Power's out in Cornbury. The Noobs just want to play video games. Shope hacks Tyler's house using Roach's Battleball. The house grows legs and arms and takes off into the sky.

35.title: Grandma Noob
35.plot: Roach's Grandma has come to visit. She mistakes Roach's ball for her broach suddenly activates its powers.

36.title: Noobs' Day Off
36.plot: Tyler has started to master his teleportation power.

37.title: The Last Noobs on Earth
37.plot: The Benevolent Alliance orders and all-out blitz to scatter the galaxy. Kevin and Roach are left on Earth to defend it.

38.title: Space Family Noobinson
38.plot: The Noobs crash land the Galacticus on a strange new world with brightly coloured plants, and have to find food and shelter on the bizarre planet they might be stuck on forever.

39.title: Electric Avenoob
39.plot: The Noobs favorite band St. Banana comes to Cornbury and they can't wait to see them.

40.title: The Green Noob
40.plot: While saving the zoo the Noobs encounter a new superhero; Green Steel. He idolizes the Noobs and tries to be just like them but ends up causing more problems.

1.title: A Noob Hope
1.plot: While playing paintball, four kids come across aliens Mem and Zen who mistake their paintball gear for warrior gear. They are then enlisted to save the earth by fighting the virus with battleballs that give them superpowers. The Supernoobs now have to learn how to use their new powers to fight a mashed potatoes virus that is destroying their school.

2.title: The Noobs Strike Back
2.plot: Mem and Zen realize their mistake in picking the Noobs and want to take the battleballs back. In order to save themselves the Noobs must go to space to plead their case to the Benevolent Alliance and keep their battleballs. There they are tested individually and judged on their abilities to fight the virus.

3.title: Super Noob Suits
3.plot: The Noobs make the Cornbury News after fighting a virus beast in the park and realize that they will need superhero costumes to hide their identity. Mem and Zen go to work finding the perfect Earth hero costumes.

4.title: Noobies vs. Smoothies
4.plot: The Noobs discover that Mem and Zen have the power to transform themselves into people and imitate their voices. Tyler goes on a date with Amy Anderson to the new smoothie shop when an active yogurt culture smoothie becomes infected with the virus.

5.title: Go Noob Outside
5.plot: Nervous that the virus could attack at any minute Kevin insists on wearing his battleball in school when it malfunctions and he gets stuck as a dog. Upon getting caught by the dog catcher and thrown in the pound the virus begins to infect the stray animals. The Noobs must find a way to free him from the pound before he is stuck that way forever while battling the Virus.

6.title: Curb Your Noob
6.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

7.title: Noob Kids on the Block
7.plot: A new strain, called the elimination virus is discovered that has the ability to infect a human without changing their appearance. In an attempt to destroy the Noobs, the virus infects the glee club and they must battle them in a sing and dance off in front of the whole school.

8.title: Fourth Down and Noob to Go
8.plot: The Noobs training continues as they learn new ways to use their powers to defeat the virus. Realizing that they could use their powers to also defeat their schools arch rivals, the Eastside Wolves, the Noobs join the football team and are faced with a moral dilemma of getting caught.

9.title: Who, What, Where and Noob
9.plot: Shope's parents are concerned about her performance in school and feel that the boys are bad influence. The Noobs sneak into the Galacticus cloaking room where the energy is transferred to Shope, making her invisible instead of the Galacticus. The boys have to keep Shope out of trouble until Mem and Zen can make her visible again.

10.title: Shake Your Noobie
10.plot: The Noobs turn to Mem and Zen to help them prepare for the upcoming school dance where a fire virus turns students into fire breathing dragons. In an effort to get closer to Amy, Tyler's plan to save her in his Supernoobs costume backfires when she falls for the super hero version of himself instead.

11.title: Where No Noob Has Gone Before
11.plot: During rehearsal for the school play where Roach plays a rocket, his battleball becomes activated by his love for the drama coach making him shoot off like a real rocket. Fearful that he will be mistaken for a real missile and shot down the Noobs must find a way to rescue him and bring him back down to Earth.

12.title: How to Care for Your Noob
12.plot: When Tyler and Shope's guinea pig escapes from home ec class Kevin has to become a guinea pig to sit in while Tyler searches for the real one. Tyler and Roach then discover a virus that recently landed only to find the guinea pig has eaten several of them. Now they must conquer the virus beats and get the guinea pig back in its cage before the end of class.

13.title: The Noobs Meet Count Venamus
13.plot: Mem and Zen take the Noobs to space for the New Virus Warrior Convention and Recruiters Awards where they are not taken seriously and spend the time in their hotel room instead. Meanwhile at the Awards Ceremony, Count Venamus is set on spreading the virus to all the new recruits leaving only the Noobs uninfected to battle the virus.

14.title: Dude, Where's My Noob
14.plot: The Benevolent Alliance has come to inspect the Noobs battleballs, the only problem is they have misplaced them. Mem and Zen fake a virus attack to stall while the Noobs retrace their steps in order to find the battleballs before the leaders discover that they have lost them.

15.title: Tyrannosaurus Noob
15.plot: While on a field trip to the museum, the Tyrannosaurus skeleton gets infected by the virus and comes to life.

16.title: When Good Noobs Go Bad
16.plot: Roach's battleball malfunctions, transforming him into an evil super villain bent on dominating the Earth

17.title: Superdoods!
17.plot: Mem and Zen decide to become directors and create a TV show based on their adventures with the Noobs

18.title: License to Noob
18.plot: The Noobs pilot the Galacticus into space to get medicine for Mem and Zen's infected eyes, and end up helping a space princess overthrow an evil dictator.

19.title: Noobot vs. Venabot
19.plot: When Count Venamus returns with a giant robot, and a plan to use a virus pod meteor shower to infect the planet, the Noobs turn the Galacticus into a giant robot to stop him.

20.title: Zooper Noobs!
20.plot: The Noobs travel to an alien zoo with Mem and Zen, only to be captured and put into a exhibit by the zoo's owner.

21.title: Noob Kid in Town
21.plot: Kevin transforms into a cat and gets stuck in a tree until a teen boy rescues him and receives a reward from the city, leading the Noobs to attempt to get the same.

22.title: Parent Teacher Noobs
22.plot: Mem and Zen pose as the Noobs' parents during parent-teacher conferences at school.

23.title: Noob It or Lose It
23.plot: The Noobs attempt to use their powers to penetrate the incredibly long line for a new video game.

24.title: Noobsitters
24.plot: The Noobs attempt to prove that they are responsible by babysitting for a couple who have just moved into the neighborhood, which becomes more difficult when the baby drinks a bottle infected with the virus.

25.title: How to Use Your Noob
25.plot: The Noobs discover that they can turn their battleballs into whatever they desire.

26.title: A Noob Divided Cannot Noob!
26.plot: The pressures of living together finally push Mem and Zen to the breaking point, causing them both to move out, and into the homes of the Noobs, who quickly grow tired of them and scheme to get the two back together.

27.title: Super Natural Noobs
27.plot: The Noobs take advantage of a lack of virus attacks by going camping, but Kevin is afraid of the Cornbury Monster who is rumored to lurk in the woods.

28.title: The Supernoobs Super Cup
28.plot: The Noobs decide to see who's the best of the group by competing in a series of events in the first ever "Supernoob Super Cup".

29.title: How to Noob the Science Fair
29.plot: The Noobs compete against each other in the school science fair, but problems arise when several of the projects are infected by the virus.

30.title: Noob Tube
30.plot: Mem and Zen try to make the Noobs seem like great warriors when they discover they will be featured on the intergalactic reality show "Extreme Virus Warriors".

31.title: The Noobie Bluebie Booby
31.plot: Roach begins to feel that the other Noobs are taking advantage of him, so when a rare bird is infected by the virus on a field trip, he decides to let the others handle it without him.

32.title: Noobs vs. The Earth-sterminator!
32.plot: The Noobs accidentally press a wrong button on the Galacticus and send a planet destroying drone toward Earth.

33.title: Noob Coloured Glasses
33.plot: Mr. Wertz's mind control goggles bring the entire town under his spell, except for Shope

34.title: Let it Noob, Let it Noob, Let it Noob!
34.plot: Mem and Zen encounter snow for the first time

35.title: To Catch a Noob
35.plot: Count Venamus hatches a plan to lock up Roach, in the hopes that it will make it easier to defeat the Noobs.

36.title: The Noobiest Place on Earth!
36.plot: While at an amusement park, the Noobs must battle virus-infected mascots.

37.title: Count Noob-A-Nus
37.plot: Count Venamus returns and strangely surrenders to the Noobs.

38.title: I Know You Noob
38.plot: After witnessing the Noobs battle a virus beast while not wearing their super suits, three little girls threaten to reveal their identities.

39.title: The Supernoobs Meet Incredibly Amazing Man
39.plot: The Noobs encounter a destructive superhero from another world.

40.title: Happy Noob-o-ween
40.plot: Mem and Zen try to grasp the concept of Halloween. The Noobs fight virus infected people wearing costumes at the Halloween festival.

41.title: The Noob Cave!
41.plot: The Noobs decide to set up their own secret base of operations so they can feel like real superheroes, but get into a fight over what their newfound lair should look like and it destroys their friendship. Mem and Zen, concerned over the Noobs destroyed relationship with each other, try to bring them all back together.

42.title: To Noob or Not to Noob
42.plot: The Noobs ponder over whether or not to use their battle ball powers during school for personal gain.

43.title: Noobie Mama
43.plot: A new strain of the virus causes the Noobs to get literally sucked into a video game.

44.title: Noobs of the Round Table
44.plot: General Blorgon and the other members of the Benevolent Alliance visit Earth to enjoy more of what Earth has to offer. They go out to a renaissance barbecue with the Noobs and Mem and Zen but things go awry when the renaissance actors get infected with the virus.

45.title: Super Noob Super Cup Redux
45.plot: The second Super Noobs Super Cup begins but this time, Mem and Zen decide to compete in it.
